 Recon-NG 

## 1. Overview
Recon-NG is a modular web reconnaissance framework similar to Metasploit, designed for automated OSINT collection.

Used in:
- Bug Bounty recon  
- Collecting emails, subdomains, credentials leaks  
- Automating passive information gathering  

## 2. Key Features
- Over 70 recon modules  
- API key support  
- Workspace-based environment  
- Data storage & exporting  
- Automated OSINT reporting  

---

## 3. Installation

### Linux / macOS
git clone https://github.com/lanmaster53/recon-ng.git
cd recon-ng
pip install -r REQUIREMENTS

### Windows

Install manually:
https://github.com/lanmaster53/recon-ng

## Common Commands
recon-ng
modules search
modules load recon/domains-hosts/bing_domain_web
keys add bing_api
run
show results

## Important Modules & Parameters
Module	                                Description
recon/domains-hosts/bing_domain_web	    Collect hosts via Bing
recon/contacts-credentials/hibp_breach	Find breached emails
recon/domains-hosts/hackertarget	      Subdomain enumeration
recon/profile/profile	User profiling
reporting/html	Generate HTML reports

Common Flags:

run – execute module

info – show module info

options set X – configure module

## Advanced Usage
Automated Full Recon Pipeline Script
workspaces create target
modules load recon/domains-hosts/hackertarget
options set SOURCE example.com
run

Export Results
reporting/json
